"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-29-fiba-ranking-dtigress-climb-to-eighth-position-after-impressive-olympic-outing\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's D'Tigress jumped four places in the latest ranking released by the Federation of International Basketball Association (FIBA) on Thursday.  D'Tigress are now ranked the eighth best team in the world.  Rena Wakama's side's rise is connected with their outstanding display in the women's basketball event at the 2024 Olympic Games in Paris.  The African champions defeated top ranked teams Australia and Canada in the group stage.  They also made history as the first African team to make it to the quarter-finals of the Olympics.  D'Tigress bowed out gallantly to holders United States of America in the last-eight.  No African team (male and female) have ever made it to the top 10 of FIBA rankings  Transfer: Osimhen reportedly agrees \\u20ac350,000-per-week deal with Chelsea  NPFL: Bayelsa United promotes two youngsters to main team  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  2026 FIBA World Cup Qualifiers: D'Tigress rally to 101-84 victory over Philippines  FIBA WWQ 2026: Gallant D'Tigress fall 77-60 to Korea  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"